data.name: AppDescription
data.value: Utility application for interacting with Windows MIDI Services from the command line. Requires that Windows MIDI Services is installed and enabled on the PC.

data.name: CommandDiagnosticsReportDescription
data.value: Generate a report, typically for a support request, or for use when filing a bug

data.name: CommandEndpointDescription
data.value: Perform operations on a single endpoint, including reporting details, sending messages, monitoring, and more. If you leave out the Instance Id, you will be prompted to select from a list.

data.name: CommandEndpointPropertiesDescription
data.value: List out all properties for a given endpoint

data.name: CommandEndpointRequestDescription
data.value: Request certain MIDI 2.0 in-protocol data from an endpoint. Use a separate console or application to view the responses.

data.name: CommandEndpointRequestEndpointMetadataDescription
data.value: Send an endpoint discovery message to the endpoint. You can monitor incoming messages in another window, or watch property changes

data.name: CommandEndpointRequestFunctionBlocksDescription
data.value: Send a function block request message to the endpoint. You can monitor incoming messages or the device properties in another window

data.name: CommandEnumerateActiveSessionsDescription
data.value: List all currently active Windows MIDI Services sessions on this PC.

data.name: CommandEnumerateEndpointsDescription
data.value: List MIDI UMP endpoints visible to Windows MIDI Services-aware applications

data.name: CommandEnumerateLegacyEndpointsDescription
data.value: List MIDI 1.0 endpoints as seen in apps using older MIDI APIs

data.name: CommandEnumerateTransportPluginsDescription
data.value: List all MIDI transport plugins installed on this PC.

data.name: CommandMonitorEndpointDescription
data.value: Monitors a UMP endpoint for incoming messages

data.name: CommandSendMessageDescription
data.value: Send a single message to a UMP endpoint as a list of up to four 32 bit MIDI words

data.name: CommandSendMessagesFileDescription
data.value: Sends a text file of UMP MIDI words to the specified endpoint. See arguments and options for format and delimiters.

data.name: CommandServiceDescription
data.value: Perform operations on the service, such as checking to see if it is running, pinging the standard ping loopback, etc.

data.name: CommandServiceRestartDescription
data.value: Restart the MIDI service. This will close all open connections, remove any non-persistent configuration, and otherwise reset the MIDI system. Must be run as Administrator.

data.name: CommandServiceStartDescription
data.value: Start the MIDI Service if it is currently stopped. Must be run as Administrator.

data.name: CommandServiceStatusDescription
data.value: Check to see if the Windows Service is running

data.name: CommandServiceStopDescription
data.value: Stops the MIDI Service, freeing up all resources in use, closing all devices, and clearing any runtime configuration. Must be run as Administrator.

data.name: CommandTimeDescription
data.value: Get the current MIDI clock timestamp value

data.name: CommandWatchEndpointsDescription
data.value: Watch endpoints for add/remove and PnP property change notifications

data.name: ErrorEnumEndpointsFailed
data.value: Enumerating endpoints failed. Is the MIDI service running?

data.name: ErrorGeneralFailReasonWinRTActivation
data.value: The WinRT types could not be activated. Is Windows MIDI Services installed?

data.name: ErrorUnableToCreateEndpointConnection
data.value: Unable to create endpoint connection. Is the endpoint Id correct? Is the type of endpoint correct?

data.name: ErrorUnableToSendMessage
data.value: Unable to send message to endpoint

data.name: FunctionBlockNumberInvalid
data.value: The function block number is invalid. Please request a number between 0 and 31, inclusive.

data.name: FunctionBlockRequestInvalid
data.value: The function block request is invalid. Please request at last one data item.

data.name: InteractiveEndpointMenuPleaseSelectOption
data.value: Please select one of the following

data.name: MessageValidationErrorInvalidUmp
data.value: The data does not result in a valid UMP

data.name: MessageValidationErrorTooFewWords
data.value: Please provide at least one valid 32-bit MIDI word

data.name: MessageValidationErrorTooManyWords
data.value: Please provide up to four valid 32-bit MIDI words, comprising a single valid UMP.

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesAnnotate
data.value: True to annotate messages written to the file. Annotations begin with the # sign and are written on the line before the UMP data line. The annotation includes timestamp information as well as the specific message type.

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesFieldDebugWarnSkippedIncrement
data.value: For incoming streams where the last word is incremented by one each time (a developer debugging approach) warn when there are gaps.

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesFieldDelimiter
data.value: Delimiter to separate fields. Valid values include:

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesFieldFormat
data.value: Format for the fields. Hex prefix is "0x", suffix is "h". Decimal values do not have leading zeroes. Valid values include:

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesFilter
data.value: Filter for the messages. Valid values include:

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesIncludeTimestamps
data.value: True to include the timestamp as the first field for each message.

data.name: ParameterCaptureMessagesOutputFile
data.value: Capture messages to the specified file. If the file exists, it will be appended to.

data.name: ParameterCommonEndpointIdDescription
data.value: Endpoint Id (also called a Device Instance Id) of the endpoint as used in Windows.Devices.Enumeration. This includes the MIDI interface GUID at the end of the string. You can find the Endpoint Ids by enumerating endpoints through this app. If you leave off the Id, we'll re-enumerate them and provide a list for you to pick from.

data.name: ParameterEndpointPropertiesIncludeRaw
data.value: Include the full list of raw property keys and values for the endpoint. Typically useful only for debugging purposes.

data.name: ParameterEndpointPropertiesVerbose
data.value: Include additional detailed information about the endpoint.

data.name: ParameterEnumEndpointsDirection
data.value: The direction of data flow for the endpoints to list

data.name: ParameterEnumEndpointsIncludeAll
data.value: List all recognized endpoints, including internal ones and ones an application may be unable to connect to directly.

data.name: ParameterEnumEndpointsIncludeEndpointId
data.value: Include the UMP Endpoint Id in the output

data.name: ParameterEnumEndpointsVerboseOutput
data.value: Include more details for each endpoint

data.name: ParameterEnumLegacyEndpointsDirection
data.value: The direction of data flow for the endpoints to list

data.name: ParameterEnumLegacyEndpointsIncludeEndpointId
data.value: Include the MIDI 1.0 Endpoint Id (the Port Id) in the output

data.name: ParameterMonitorEndpointAutoReconnect
data.value: Continue monitoring and automatically reconnect after device disconnection, if device becomes available (unplug/replug).

data.name: ParameterMonitorEndpointDirectionDescription
data.value: The direction of the endpoint referenced by the Id. If this doesn't match the endpoint type, the connection will fail.

data.name: ParameterMonitorEndpointSingleMessage
data.value: Wait for a single incoming message only

data.name: ParameterMonitorEndpointSkipToKeepUp
data.value: If you are monitoring very fast input from a device, the display can start to lag behind considerably. In that case, set this to true and messages will be skipped (only on the display output) to try to keep the display output roughly in time with the messages received.

data.name: ParameterMonitorEndpointVerbose
data.value: Provide additional columns of information for each message

data.name: ParameterRequestEndpointMetadataEndpointNameNotification
data.value: Request an endpoint name notification. May result in multiple response messages.

data.name: ParameterRequestEndpointMetadataEndpointProductInstanceIdNotification
data.value: Request a product instance id notification. May result in multiple response messages.

data.name: ParameterRequestEndpointMetadataEndpointUmpVersionMajor
data.value: The UMP specification major version. The default is usually sufficient.

data.name: ParameterRequestEndpointMetadataEndpointUmpVersionMinor
data.value: The UMP specification minor version. The default is usually sufficient.

data.name: ParameterRequestFunctionBlockInfoNotification
data.value: Request the general information for a function block

data.name: ParameterRequestFunctionBlockNameNotification
data.value: Request the name for a function block

data.name: ParameterRequestFunctionBlockNumber
data.value: Request just the specified function block number

data.name: ParameterRequestFunctionBlocksAll
data.value: Request all function blocks for this endpoint

data.name: ParameterSendMessageAutoIncrementLastWord
data.value: This is for developers and those who want to check that all messages are being sent/received in the correct order. When set, it will auto-increment the last word you have specified by 1 for each message sent. Requires that a message of two or more words be used so that the message type nibble isn't impacted.

data.name: ParameterSendMessageCount
data.value: Number of times to send this message

data.name: ParameterSendMessageDelayBetweenMessages
data.value: Delay, in milliseconds, between messages. This is an approximate delay. Specify 0 for no delay.

data.name: ParameterSendMessageEndpointDirectionDescription
data.value: The direction of the endpoint referenced by the Id. If this doesn't match the endpoint type, the connection will fail.

data.name: ParameterSendMessagesFileCommandFile
data.value: Path and filename of the text file to send. This can include lines which begin with # for a comment, or are completely empty for spacing. Remaining lines must be valid delimited (big-endian) hexadecimal UMP words.

data.name: ParameterSendMessagesFileFieldDelimiter
data.value: Delimiter between fields. Set to "Auto" to have this evaluated for each line. Valid values include:

data.name: ParameterSendMessagesFileReplaceGroup
data.value: For non-stream messages, replace the second nibble with the specified new group index. Helpful when sending previously-recorded SysEx to a new group.

data.name: ParameterSendMessagesFileVerbose
data.value: Verbose output as the messages are sent

data.name: ParameterSendMessageTimestamp
data.value: Absolute timestamp value to use for all messages. User 0 to bypass scheduling and send immediately.

data.name: ParameterSendMessageTimestampOffsetMicroseconds
data.value: Timestamp offset in microseconds (1/1,000,000 of a second) to use when scheduling this message. A new timestamp with this offset is calculated for each sent message as it is sent.

data.name: ParameterSendMessageWordFormat
data.value: Data format for the individual words. Valid values include:

data.name: ParameterSendMessageWords
data.value: 32-bit MIDI words, typically in hexadecimal 0x00000000 format. Big-endian, same as the MIDI protocol wire format. Use the parameter name in front of each word sent.

data.name: ParameterServicePingCount
data.value: Number of times to ping the MIDI Windows Service

data.name: ParameterServicePingTimeout
data.value: Total ping timeout in milliseconds. Does not include the session and connection creation and teardown time.

data.name: ParameterServicePingVerbose
data.value: True to show details from each ping request and response.

data.name: ParameterServiceStatusVerbose
data.value: Report additional details about the service

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionActiveConfiguration
data.value: From endpoint discovery and protocol negotiation and represent the current configuration of the endpoint.

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionContainer
data.value: The container is how Windows groups related devices

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionDeclaredCapabilities
data.value: From endpoint discovery and protocol negotiation and represent the capabilities of the endpoint.

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionEndpointMetadata
data.value: Metadata captured using MIDI 2.0 endpoint discovery

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionFunctionBlocks
data.value: Function blocks are discovered through endpoint discovery in-protocol.

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionParentDevice
data.value: The device which "owns" this endpoint. In some cases, this is a software device.

data.name: PropertyTableSectionDescriptionTransportInformation
data.value: From the transport plugin in the service (and from the driver in cases where a driver is used)

data.name: PropertyTableSectionNoteGTBFunctionBlocksAlsoPresent
data.value: Function blocks are also present, and will be more accurate.

data.name: PropertyValueNativeDataFormatUmp
data.value: Universal MIDI Packet (MIDI 1.0 or MIDI 2.0 protocol)

data.name: SendMessageEscapePressedMessage
data.value: Escape key pressed. Message sending terminated.

data.name: SendMessageFloodWarning
data.value: Warning: sending a large number of messages with no delay can result in flooding the buffers. This is especially true of software endpoints like the loopback, or slow external hardware. Message loss may result.

data.name: SendMessagePressEscapeToStopSendingMessage
data.value: Press escape to stop sending messages.

data.name: ValidationErrorInvalidGroup
data.value: The specified group index is invalid. Specify a group index between 0 and 15.

data.name: ValidationErrorPingCountTooHigh
data.value: Specified ping count is too high. Please provide a value <= 255.

data.name: ValidationErrorPingCountTooLow
data.value: Specified ping count is too low. Please provide a value > 0.

data.name: ValidationErrorPingTimeoutTooLow
data.value: Specified timeout is too low. Please provide a value >= 10ms.

data.name: WatcherEscapePressedMessage
data.value: Escape key pressed. Shutting down watcher.

data.name: WatcherPressEscapeToStopWatchingMessage
data.value: Press escape to stop watching for endpoint changes.

data.name: CommandSendSysExFileDescription
data.value: Send a file of MIDI 1.0 or MIDI 2.0 SysEx messages (7 or 8 bit, binary or text) to a compatible endpoint.

data.name: ErrorMidiServiceNotAvailable
data.value: The MIDI Service is not available.

data.name: ErrorSdkInitializationFailed
data.value: Windows MIDI Services SDK runtime failed to initialize. Is it installed?

data.name: ErrorSdkInitializerInitializationFailed
data.value: Failed to start up the SDK initializer (COM object may not be available or registered)

data.name: CommandEnumerateMdnsAdvertisementsDescription
data.value: List discovered MDNS advertisements for Network MIDI 2.0 (UDP) services on the network.

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesIndexes
data.value: List of space-separated MIDI 1.0 note indexes (0-127 decimal)

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesLengthMilliseconds
data.value: Length / duration of the note in whole decimal milliseconds.

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesGroupNumber
data.value: Number (1-16 decimal) for the group to send the messages to

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesChannelNumber
data.value: Number (1-16 decimal) of the channel to send the messages to

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesVelocity
data.value: Note velocity (1.0 - 100.0) as a fractional decimal percentage of the maximum value for the protocol.

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesForever
data.value: Set to true to continue to loop through the notes until you press the escape key

data.name: CommandPlayNotesDescription
data.value: Send MIDI 1.0 or 2.0 note on and off messages to the endpoint

data.name: CommandEnumerateEndpointPropertyKeysDescription
data.value: List the Windows MIDI Services-specific property keys

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesRestMilliseconds
data.value: Duration of wait time between notes, in whole decimal milliseconds

data.name: ParameterPlayNotesMidi2
data.value: Set to true to use MIDI 2.0 protocol messages (type 4) instead of MIDI 1.0 protocol (type 2)

data.name: ServiceSetAutoDelayedStartDescription
data.value: Set the MIDI Service to start shortly after Windows starts, to avoid connection delays with the first connection made by an app.
